ough as a couple, reality shows can be a good thing for the relationship.', 58431, 0), (491245, 'Each brand leader is focused on ensuring that the brand relationship with its customer is strong and differentiated. To accomplish this differentiation, we plan to offer her even more unique product and talk with her in new and exciting ways.', 67134, 0), (491246, 'For me, writing is a love-hate relationship.', 18449, 0), (491247, 'I don''t even like to use the word relationship. I don''t know what it means.', 67791, 0), (491248, 'In a relationship you have to open yourself up.', 51029, 0), (491249, 'My parents and I didn''t speak for 10 years. It took a long time to rebuild that relationship.', 70600, 0), (491250, 'Therapy is not to ''talk about'' things, but to change the person''s life, and to relieve suffering, such as depression, anxiety, or relationship problems.', 11168, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (491251, 'I think to make any relationship work it just takes a tremendous amount of effort and accepting of one another.', 68544, 0), (491252, 'Men should only believe half of what women say. But which half?', 42142, 0), (491253, 'Yes, I don''t believe that the inter-Korean relationship has, quote, ''deteriorated'' since I assumed office. Rather I believe that the relationship between the two Koreas is entering into a new phase - a time of transition. And so I think that the North Koreans are trying to see what they can build with this, with my new administration.', 50249, 0), (491254, 'I couldn''t be in a relationship and behave like somebody else or pretend I felt something I didn''t feel. And that includes saying things I thought might jeopardize the relationship.', 71326, 0), (491255, 'There''s no shortage of orphans in 19th-century literature, but it''s hard to find a single happy, communicative, functional parental relationship in the whole of ''Great Expectations,'' even among the minor characters.', 158, 0), (491256, 'I don''t know if there is a ''lack'' of good black men. But when you haven''t taken the time to get to know yourself, be OK with you, and articulate what it is you want in a relationship, then you can''t possibly find that person for you because you don''t even know what you''re looking for.', 73610, 0), (491257, 'My ideal relationship with the reader is that at certain points they will have said, ''I''m finding this quite tough, but I''m going to hang in there,'' then at the end they will say, ''Oh God, I''m glad I hung on, it was so worth it.''', 6038, 0), (491258, 'We all have something about ourselves that we''d change if we could in a perfect world, be it our body image, our financial status, our relationship, whatever. I wanted to talk about how nobody''s exempted from the realities of life and all those things.', 75824, 0), (491259, 'I am not possessive at all. In every relationship I have had, the girl has left me. And the fundamental complaint has been that I am self-contained. I am just comfortable with myself and am always on an adventure.', 74141, 0), (491260, 'Every relationship I''ve been in becomes long-distance because of work. It''s never worked out. It puts an intense strain on the relationship, and at a certain point, it becomes too difficult.', 75825, 0), (491261, 'If a relationship is founded on love it doesn''t end.', 63152, 0), (491262, 'I always felt sorry for the sidekick as a kid. They never got their due and it left a very bad taste in the mouth - they are defined by a subordinate relationship to someone else. I always felt like a bit of sidekick when I was a kid and it didn''t feel fair.', 1808, 0), (491263, 'The grief of losing my father has come in waves over the years, as it does with most people. His love and devotion as a father provided my closest, most intimate relationship. Dad, and our time together, is in my bones. While reflecting on him, the memories themselves seem to boil down into certain ''essences of Dad.''', 68368, 0), (491264, 'What I learned from directing, I learned from soccer, where it''s like a coach-player relationship.', 72005, 0), (491265, 'The Thames could be thought of as England''s longest archaeological site, and no fewer than 90,000 objects recovered from its foreshore are in the collection of the Museum of London, whose 30-year relationship with London mudlarks is both committed and highly regulated.', 15571, 0), (491266, 'When I sit down to write a novel, I am exploring my own relationship with God, with the struggle between good and evil, my own purpose.', 1986, 0), (491267, 'The value of government to the people it serves is in direct relationship to the interest citizens themselves display in the affairs of state.', 71998, 0), (491268, 'The relationship with the words someone uses is more intimate and integrated than just a quick read and a blurb can ever be. This intimacy - the words on the page being sent back and forth from engaged editor to open author - is unique in my experience.', 1279, 0), (491269, 'And harmony means that the relationship between all the elements used in a composition is balanced, is good.', 71748, 0), (491270, 'A Bush Administration will, I believe, enjoy a better relationship with the new Congress, although President-elect Bush will be faced with real challenges in getting along with the Congress.', 73321, 0), (491271, 'The key to successful missionary work is a close relationship between the missionaries and the members. Creating an environment in working with members that will bring more into the Church.', 4139, 0), (491272, 'Cinema for me only has meaning when it has a relationship with what I see outside on the street.', 74560, 0), (491273, 'I wish I had a great relationship with my mother.', 75826, 0), (491274, 'When you''re watching television, you don''t want to watch a show where everything just works out. You don''t want to see a relationship that''s just blossoming and everyone''s happy and sunshine and roses all the time. That''s also not true in life.', 74305, 0), (491275, 'I think that the two of them have been doing this for a really long time and it is more like sport. Yes, they would love to find a lasting relationship, but it''s not likely to happen the way they are going about it.', 75148, 0), (491276, 'I think it''s healthy for couples to be away from each other for short periods.', 69252, 0), (491277, 'I don''t think it''s necessarily healthy to go into relationships as a needy person. Better to go in with a full deck.', 57967, 0), (491278, 'People who supported Obama felt like they formed a relationship, that they were being spoken to. The way that campaign worked and the way he''s worked during his first term is to make people feel like he''s grasping their hand, whether it''s by tweeting or email, moments after an event, sometimes during an event. It makes people relate to him.', 74534, 0), (491