INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (491901, 'Sri Lanka is an island that everyone loves at some level inside themselves. A very special island that travellers, from Sinbad to Marco Polo, dreamed about. A place where the contours of the land itself forms a kind of sinewy poetry.', 72378, 0), (491902, 'If what distinguishes us from other species is speech, then poetry, which is the supreme linguistic operation, is our anthropological - indeed, genetic - goal.', 1254, 0), (491903, 'I cannot speak for more than an hour exclusively about poetry. At that point, life itself takes over again.', 23289, 0), (491904, 'Spoken word poetry is the art of performance poetry. I tell people it involves creating poetry that doesn''t just want to sit on paper, that something about it demands it be heard out loud or witnessed in person.', 308, 0), (491905, 'Poetry is what we do to break bread with the dead.', 1422, 0), (491906, 'The poets have been mysteriously silent on the subject of cheese.', 67663, 0), (491907, 'Who writes poetry imbibes honey from the poisoned lips of life.', 75871, 0), (491908, 'He who draws noble delights from sentiments of poetry is a true poet, though he has never written a line in all his life.', 810, 0), (491909, 'A poem is never finished, only abandoned.', 3087, 0), (491910, 'I have been enlightened. I have fallen into poetry and it has swallowed me up.', 19934, 0), (491911, 'The drama is complete poetry. The ode and the epic contain it only in germ; it contains both of them in a state of high development, and epitomizes both.', 98, 0), (491912, 'I consider myself a poet first and a musician second. I live like a poet and I''ll die like a poet.', 289, 0), (491913, 'Poetry is the opening and closing of a door, leaving those who look through to guess about what is seen during the moment.', 1301, 0), (491914, 'I have nothing to say, I am saying it, and that is poetry.', 1931, 0), (491915, 'The poet may be used as a barometer, but let us not forget that he is also part of the weather.', 13991, 0), (491916, 'Breathe-in experience, breathe-out poetry.', 1736, 0), (491917, 'To read a poem is to hear it with our eyes to hear it is to see it with our ears. ', 8633, 0), (491918, 'Poetry is a mirror which makes beautiful that which is distorted.', 165, 0), (491919, 'God is the perfect poet.', 698, 0), (491920, 'One will never again look at a birch tree, after the Robert Frost poem, in exactly the same way.', 71029, 0), (491921, 'I still read Donne, particularly his love poems.', 7418, 0), (491922, 'As human beings, we are the only organisms that create for the sheer stupid pleasure of doing so. Whether it''s laying out a garden, composing a new tune on the piano, writing a bit of poetry, manipulating a digital photo, redecorating a room, or inventing a new chili recipe - we are happiest when we are creating.', 30035, 0), (491923, 'The genesis of a poem for me is usually a cluster of words. The only good metaphor I can think of is a scientific one: dipping a thread into a supersaturated solution to induce crystal formation. I don''t think I solve problems in my poetry I think I uncover the problems. ', 114, 0), (491924, 'I''ve written some poetry I don''t understand myself.', 1301, 0), (491925, 'Poetry is a sword of lightning, ever unsheathed, which consumes the scabbard that would contain it.', 165, 0), (491926, 'Drawing is a way of coming upon the connection between things, just like metaphor in poetry reconnects what has become separated.', 1307, 0), (491927, 'Poetry begins where language starts: in the shadows and accidents of one person''s life.', 8802, 0), (491928, 'I have been writing poetry for a long time now. I started writing in my school days.', 69732, 0), (491929, 'The true spirit of delight, the exaltation, the sense of being more than Man, which is the touchstone of the highest excellence, is to be found in mathematics as surely as poetry.', 95, 0), (491930, 'Great poetry is always written by somebody straining to go beyond what he can do.', 37854, 0), (491931, 'Most people read poetry listening for echoes because the echoes are familiar to them. They wade through it the way a boy wades through water, feeling with his toes for the bottom: The echoes are the bottom.', 2547, 0), (491932, 'Poetry should help, not only to refine the language of the time, but to prevent it from changing too rapidly.', 1067, 0), (491933, 'The only thing that can save the world is the reclaiming of the awareness of the world. That''s what poetry does.', 478, 0), (491934, 'Poetry is not an expression of the party line. It''s that time of night, lying in bed, thinking what you really think, making the private world public, that''s what the poet does.', 478, 0), (491935, 'We make out of the quarrel with others, rhetoric, but of the quarrel with ourselves, poetry.', 62867, 0), (491936, 'I don''t think you get to good writing unless you expose yourself and your feelings. Deep songs don''t come from the surface; they come from the deep down. The poetry and the songs that you are suppose to write, I believe are in your heart.', 7212, 0), (491937, 'Theater and poetry were what helped people stay alive and want to go on living.', 75869, 0), (491938, 'Poetry involves the mysteries of the irrational perceived through rational words.', 76, 0), (491939, 'In poetry, you must love the words, the ideas and the images and rhythms with all your capacity to love anything at all.', 2547, 0), (491940, 'That''s the way it is with poetry: When it is incomprehensible it seems profound, and when you understand it, it is only ridiculous.', 8074, 0), (491941, 'Poetry is as precise a thing as geometry.', 647, 0), (491942, 'I''m sorry, man, but I''ve got magic. I''ve got poetry in my fingertips. Most of the time - and this includes naps - I''m an F-18, bro. And I will destroy you in the air. I will deploy my ordinance to the ground.', 23240, 0), (491943, 'In the language of poetry, where every word is weighed, nothing is usual or normal. Not a single stone and not a single cloud above it. Not a single day and not a single night after it. And above all, not a single existence, not anyone''s existence in this world.', 23289, 0), (491944, 'You know, people speak in poetry all the time. They just don''t realize it.', 360, 0), (491945, 'I don''t think I''ve ever read poetry, ever.', 392, 0), (491946, 'I have piles of poetry books in the bathroom, on the stairs, everywhere. The only way to write poetry is to read it.', 7418, 0), (491947, 'If you don''t mark your successes, the day your ship comes in could be just another day at the office, and there''s no poetry in that.', 73227, 0), (491948, 'It is certain that at certain times talent entirely overcomes thought or poetry.', 63828, 0), (491949, 'If you''ve ever been to a poetry slam, you know that the highest scoring emotion is self-righteous indignation: how dare you judge me. So in that way, the poem, ''What Teachers Make,'' is an absolutely formulaic slam poem designed to allow me to get up on my soap box and say, ''Let me tell you what really makes me angry.''', 776, 0), (491950, 'When I rap, I get to express myself in a way where putting words together is like poetry, and sometimes it''s better to talk in certain expressions than sing, you know? So I love, I love to rhyme when I want to express certain things.', 33126, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (491951, 'I don''t think I''ve ever read poetry, ever. I''m not really book-smart.', 392, 0), (491952, 'I think it''s often assumed that the role of poetry is to comfort, but for me, poetry is the great unsettler. It questions the established order of the mind. It is radical, by which I don''t mean that it is either leftwing or rightwing, but that it works at the roots of thinking.', 71066, 0), (491953, 'If poetry and the arts do anything, they can fortify your inner life, your inwardness.', 1422, 0), (491954, 'Everybody interprets things differently with their own perception, and I want poetry to pull out of them their own feelings.', 72461, 0), (491955, 'Poetry, at its best, is the language your soul would speak if you could teach your soul to speak.', 2687, 0), (491956, 'I''m reading a lot of poetry because it''s a lot easier to dip in and dip out when you''ve got 10 minutes to yourself.', 70665, 0), (491957, 'Music has a poetry of its own, and that poetry is called melody.', 75872, 0), (491958, 'People wish to be poets more than they wish to write poetry, and that''s a mistake. One should wish to celebrate more than one wishes to be celebrated.', 1707, 0), (491959, 'If there''s no money in poetry, neither is there poetry in money.', 8646, 0), (491960, 'I guess I wanted to leave America for awhile. It wasn''t that I wanted to become an expatriate, or just never come back, I needed some breathing room. I''d already been translating French poetry, I''d been to Paris once before and liked it very much, and so I just went.', 496, 0), (491961, 'The music just tends to be a vehicle for that poetry.', 7033, 0), (491962, 'Literature is a state of culture, poetry is a state of grace, before and after culture.', 1885, 0), (491963, 'I think the first time I really heard poetry was in the schoolyard. Just the little limericks that kids say when they''re jumping rope and playing games. I think that''s the first time I heard rhyming words - I don''t know if I''d call that the definitive poetry, but that''s when I heard rhyming words said and not necessarily sung.', 70444, 0), (491964, 'What are the sources of poetry? Love and death and the paradox of love and death. All poetry from the beginning is about Eros and Thanatos. Those are the only subjects. And how Eros and Thanatos interweave.', 405, 0), (491965, 'More modern poetry is written than read.', 10731, 0), (491966, 'Poetry at its best can do you a lot of harm.', 140, 0), (491967, 'Jazz and poetry both involve a structure that may be familiar and to some extent predictable. And then, you try to create as much surprise and spontaneity and feeling and variation while respecting that structure.', 8985, 0), (491968, 'I was raised on songs of poetry like Simon and Garfunkel and Cat Stevens and Neil Young, etc. I love those old songs probably the most because they hit me so deep down in my core.', 75873, 0), (491969, 'When you write, it''s just a much more crystalline, compressed version of the voice you think with - though not the one you speak with. I think your writing voice is your laser-guided missile. It''s the poetry part of you.', 1002, 0), (491970, 'Maya Angelou was the voice of three generations. Her poetry spanned our journey, chronicled our hearts and documented our struggles as we moved from the orations of Martin Luther King to the presidency of Barack Obama.', 67006, 0), (491971, 'Poetry is the universal language which the heart holds with nature and itself. He who has a contempt for poetry, cannot have much respect for himself, or for anything else.', 8948, 0), (491972, 'In the television age, the key distinction is between the candidate who can speak poetry and the one who can only speak prose.', 9695, 0), (491973, 'I recently read that it''s the left brain that does all that calculating, and the right brain that does the poetry. Somehow I''ve veered way towards the left. I''ve been doing it for years. Maybe I do art to balance it out.', 397, 0), (491974, 'When I was 18, I took a trip to Thailand with a friend. We stayed for a month. Bangkok was very raw for a teenager: there were no cellphones, no Internet, and the only music I had with me was this cassette by Liz Phair. I was writing a lot of poetry, and she embodied a talky style of songwriting that I found very accessible.', 67397, 0), (491975, 'In a way, Anglo-Saxon poetry cannot be translated.', 1422, 0), (491976, 'No poetry that I''m aware of, however bad or glorious, has ever left somebody a worse person than they were before they read it.', 67811, 0), (491977, 'What my character is or how many jails I have lounged in, or wards or walls or wassails, how many lonely-heart poetry readings I have dodged, is beside the point. A man''s soul or lack of it will be evident with what he can carve upon a white sheet of paper.', 78, 0), (491978, 'If the object of poetry is, to make men, then poetry is the heir of prophecy.', 8809, 0), (491979, 'Living here on Earth, we breathe the rhythms of a universe that extends infinitely above us. When resonant harmonies arise between this vast outer cosmos and the inner human cosmos, poetry is born.', 1750, 0), (491980, 'But I liked Yeats! That wild Irishman. I really loved his love of language, his flow. His chaotic ideas seemed to me just the right thing for a poet. Passion! He was always on the right side. He may be wrongheaded, but his heart was always on the right side. He wrote beautiful poetry.', 9773, 0), (491981, 'Alchemy is the art of far and near, and I think poetry is alchemy in that way. It''s delightful to distort size, to see something that''s tiny as though it were vast.', 68479, 0), (491982, 'Poetry is not only a set of words which are chosen to relate to each other it is something which goes much further than that to provide a glimpse of our vision of the world. ', 31617, 0), (491983, 'Shakespeare was a man who wrote poetry. I''m a man who writes poetry. Why not compare yourself to the best?', 8650, 0), (491984, 'Poetry fettered, fetters the human race. Nations are destroyed or flourish in proportion as their poetry, painting, and music are destroyed or flourish.', 221, 0), (491985, 'It is time to get drunk! So as not to be the martyred slaves of Time, get drunk; get drunk without stopping! On wine, on poetry, or on virtue, as you wish.', 1165, 0), (491986, 'I''ve written poetry since I was in the first grade, and it wasn''t until I was a little bit older that I realized poetry could be put to music and become a song.', 67069, 0), (491987, 'I am two fools, I know, for loving, and for saying so in whining poetry.', 703, 0), (491988, 'I saw the gooseflesh on my skin. I did not know what made it. I was not cold. Had a ghost passed over? No, it was the poetry.', 140, 0), (491989, 'How can any one paint who cannot grade colors? How can any one write poetry who has not learnt to hear and see?', 11408, 0), (491990, 'Naming a baby is an act of poetry, for many people the only creative moment of their lives.', 21677, 0), (491991, 'All slang is metaphor, and all metaphor is poetry.', 67663, 0), (491992, 'In the total darkness, poetry is still there, and it is there for you.', 21523, 0), (491993, 'If I read a book and it makes my whole body so cold no fire can ever warm me, I know that is poetry.', 91, 0), (491994, 'Everything one invents is true, you may be perfectly sure of that. Poetry is as precise as geometry.', 647, 0), (491995, 'Poetry should surprise by a fine excess and not by singularity, it should strike the reader as a wording of his own highest thoughts, and appear almost a remembrance.', 191, 0), (491996, 'The reason why we do maths is because it''s like poetry. It''s about patterns, and that really turned me on. It made me feel that maths was in tune with the other things I liked doing.', 7518, 0), (491997, 'Let''s detox our cluttered academic brain. That''s what the poet does. People call it daydreaming, detoxing our minds and taking care of that clutter. It''s being able to let in call letters from the poetry universe.', 8822, 0), (491998, 'A poet must be a psychologist, but a secret one: he should know and feel the roots of phenomena but present only the phenomena themselves in full bloom or as they fade away.', 2629, 0), (491999, 'The poetry you read has been written for you, each of you - black, white, Hispanic, man, woman, gay, straight.', 74, 0), (492000, 'Poetry comes alive to me through recitation.', 75874, 0);
